<!-- Game Description Table -->

<table class="tablestyle" id="table14" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="0">
	<tr>
		<td class="sectional">

<!-- Game Description Header -->
		
		<table class="headertable" id="table15" cellspacing="2" cellpadding="2">
			<tr>
				<td class="headercell">
				<img border="0" src="../../../images/headers/gamedes.jpg" width="240" height="33"></td>
			</tr>
		</table>

<!-- Game Description Sectional -->

<table border="0" width="100%" id="table16" cellpadding="0">
	<tr>
		<td style="font-family: Trebuchet MS; font-size: 8pt; color: #FFFFFF; font-weight: bold; text-align: left; background-color: #333333; border-left: 2px solid #000000; border-right: 2px solid #FFFFFF; border-top: 2px solid #000000; border-bottom: 2px solid #FFFFFF">
			<br>Colin McRae Rally is a rally racing game from Codemasters. The game features the popular European style of racing: rallying. When you rally race, there is only one car on the track, yours. You must race against the clock and the other times put up by the other cars. To win, you must get the best time.
			<br><br>Colin McRae Rally has a number of different modes to keep you busy. There is the championship mode, the time-trial, the rally, or rally school.
			<br><br>The first option that any racer should pursue is rally school. Here, much like in games like Gran Turismo, you must perform different activities. For example, you have to race around a loop a bunch of times without hitting too many cones. Another activity is for you to hit a high speed and then stop in a marked-off area. There are three levels of difficulty here: novice, intermediate, and expert. As the difficulty increases, the tasks become harder. The school itself shows a picture of a television with Colin McRae Rally on it. Colin McRae tells you what you must do in order to complete the task.
			<br><br>The big part of the game is the championship mode. Here you race in eight different countries. Each country has six stages and four countries have an extra stage. To move onto a new country, you must be in the top six places. The rally mode allows you to play a single country rally, by yourself or against another person. The time trial allows you to play any stage of a country rally by yourself or with someone else.
			<br><br>There are a number of different cars to choose from, including a Subaru, a Ford, and a Mitsubishi. During the game, Nicky Grist, a real-life co-driver, tells you how the road is going to be turning, which helps you in your quest to be number one.
			<br><br>Features:
			<br><br>* Race on 48 rally tracks in three countries
			<br>* Challenge a friend in split-screen two-player mode
			<br>* Eleven authentically recreated Rally vehicles
                  <br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<u>Manufacturer's description:</u><br>
                  <br>European rally racing. It'll turn you inside out and suck every ounce of adrenaline you have. It's totally unforgiving. But you'll love every second of it!
                  <br><br>* Ice, snow, gravel, tarmac and muc. If you can't handle it...go home!
                  <br>* Round the world racing. 8 countries. 48 grinding international courses.
                  <br>* 11 precisely modeled World Rally cars
                  <br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<u>Features:</u><br>
			<ul><li>Third or First person perspectives.</li>
			<li>3D graphics</li>
			<li>Cartoon graphics</li>			
			<li>Rally racing theme.</li></ul>
</td>

	</tr>
	</table>
	       	</td>
     </tr>
</table>  

